WEBVTT

00:06.215 --> 00:09.008
♪<i> I'm getting the mail,</i>
<i> hallelujah</i> ♪

00:09.093 --> 00:10.259
♪<i> I'm getting the mail</i> ♪

00:10.386 --> 00:12.136
♪<i> it's something to do.</i> ♪

00:12.221 --> 00:15.347
Hmm. What the helen mirren?

00:16.100 --> 00:18.017
Stimulus checks?

00:18.144 --> 00:21.311
We were supposed to cash these
during the pandemic.

00:21.397 --> 00:24.106
Should we spend the money now
or wait for the next one?

00:24.150 --> 00:26.775
So what are we gonna blow it on,
jet ski or motorbike?

00:26.861 --> 00:28.318
Vroom, vroom, vroom!

00:29.280 --> 00:32.156
Mom, there is something I've
always wanted for this family,

00:32.199 --> 00:34.116
But it's not a thing, exactly...

00:34.201 --> 00:35.868
Vroom?
-...But rather,

00:35.911 --> 00:37.536
It's an experience.

00:37.663 --> 00:38.746
Something we can all treasure

00:38.831 --> 00:40.664
And talk about
for years to come.

00:40.750 --> 00:42.166
Wow.

00:42.293 --> 00:44.126
Well, then maybe
we should do it.

00:44.211 --> 00:45.794
Wait, that's the move?

00:45.880 --> 00:48.172
Go all sincere and emo? Gross.

00:48.299 --> 00:50.049
Vroom, vroom, vroom,
vroom, vroom, vroom, vroom.

00:50.134 --> 00:52.134
There is one small issue.

00:52.261 --> 00:55.721
My idea will take
some finessing with dad.

00:55.806 --> 00:56.847
Hmm.

00:56.932 --> 00:59.183
Oh boy, oh boy, oh boy!

00:59.268 --> 01:01.894
Surprise money,
then a surprise cruise?

01:01.979 --> 01:04.855
Two is the perfect number
of surprises.

01:04.982 --> 01:07.983
It sure is, dad.
We're going on a regular cruise

01:08.069 --> 01:10.986
With absolutely nothing about it
you'd hate.

01:11.030 --> 01:14.073
What the hell is wrong
with this boat?

01:14.200 --> 01:16.116
[homer whimpers]

01:16.202 --> 01:19.119
"the<i> pacific princess leia</i>
is a cruise by and for

01:19.163 --> 01:21.163
"fans of sci-fi, fantasy,

01:21.290 --> 01:24.208
Comic books,
anime and video games."

01:24.293 --> 01:28.003
But-but those are all just
different names for...

01:28.089 --> 01:31.173
♪<i> nerds</i> ♪

01:31.300 --> 01:35.594
♪<i> exciting and new</i> ♪

01:35.638 --> 01:39.598
♪<i> play pickleball</i> ♪

01:39.767 --> 01:43.602
♪<i> with doctor who</i> ♪

01:43.729 --> 01:47.022
♪<i> the nerd boat</i> ♪

01:47.149 --> 01:51.485
♪<i> your wolverine t-shirt</i>
<i> is like a tux</i> ♪

01:51.612 --> 01:54.404
♪<i> the nerd boat</i> ♪

01:54.532 --> 01:59.743
♪<i> where everyone</i>
<i>knows the new star wars sucks</i> ♪

01:59.870 --> 02:01.537
♪<i> the drinks are all virgin</i> ♪

02:01.580 --> 02:05.666
♪<i> just like</i>
<i> all the guests on board</i> ♪

02:05.709 --> 02:08.585
♪<i> too busy geeking on movies</i> ♪

02:08.629 --> 02:12.673
♪<i> from miller and lord</i> ♪

02:13.634 --> 02:16.510
♪<i> and nerds</i> ♪

02:17.596 --> 02:20.139
♪<i> won't hurt anymore</i> ♪

02:21.058 --> 02:25.602
♪<i> that's a vow from your crew</i> ♪

02:25.688 --> 02:29.481
♪<i> the fantastic four</i> ♪

02:29.525 --> 02:33.902
♪<i> you're nerds</i> ♪

02:34.029 --> 02:39.992
♪<i> welcome aboard, you nerds.</i> ♪

02:40.119 --> 02:41.285
Stop this loving homage!

02:41.370 --> 02:42.786
I see what you're doing--

02:42.913 --> 02:46.039
Celebrating outcast culture
that used to be on the fringes--

02:46.167 --> 02:47.666
And I don't like it!

02:47.751 --> 02:49.293
You nerds stop playing dress-up

02:49.420 --> 02:52.078
Or else I'm gonna wedgie you,
and swirly you,

02:52.173 --> 02:53.755
And purple your nurples
until they--

02:53.883 --> 02:55.632
[moans]

02:56.635 --> 02:59.595
Hey, check out that<i> avatar</i>
volleyball tournament.

02:59.638 --> 03:02.097
It's na'vi vs. Last airbenders.

03:04.268 --> 03:06.476
And I'll be on
the "harvey" deck.

03:07.730 --> 03:10.397
Look at all those cadburys.

03:10.524 --> 03:11.857
Mmm.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.610
Oh, my god,
is that taika waititi?

03:14.737 --> 03:15.736
[giggles]

03:15.863 --> 03:17.863
I love everything you do.

03:18.032 --> 03:20.365
Your thor movies,
<i> what we do in the shadows.</i>

03:20.451 --> 03:24.995
[gasps] oh, and you're by far
my favorite on-screen hitler.

03:25.122 --> 03:26.538
Take that, the late bruno ganz.

03:26.707 --> 03:29.458
Well, if you loved that, you'll
certainly be in a "führer"

03:29.543 --> 03:32.502
Over my newest acting role
as daerius d'avignon,

03:32.671 --> 03:37.007
Medieval d'tective, in the new
$300 million streaming show

03:37.134 --> 03:39.218
<i> Murder, he swords.</i>

03:40.179 --> 03:42.638
The murderer is...
The black plague.

03:42.765 --> 03:44.097
Again.

03:44.141 --> 03:45.474
[groans]

03:45.601 --> 03:48.977
You know it's good because
it's based on existing I.P.

03:49.146 --> 03:50.979
[trance-like]
I.P., I.P.

03:51.148 --> 03:52.898
[maggie sucks pacifier]

03:52.942 --> 03:55.817
[announcer]
<i> please welcome the king</i>
<i> and queen of this nerd prom:</i>

03:55.861 --> 03:58.445
<i> Comic and kumiko book guy.</i>

03:59.782 --> 04:02.241
Out of my way,
league of non-legends.

04:02.326 --> 04:04.534
Gaze upon your betters and weep.

04:04.662 --> 04:06.495
Behold,

04:06.580 --> 04:09.081
I have brought the jewel of
my collectible collection.

04:09.166 --> 04:11.959
The rarest treasure
in all of geekdom:

04:12.044 --> 04:14.294
A radioactive man action figure

04:14.380 --> 04:17.756
Accidentally manufactured
with wolverine claws.

04:17.883 --> 04:21.009
Gaze upon it
and lose your mind.

04:21.095 --> 04:23.303
[cheering and applause]

04:23.430 --> 04:25.013
Only two of those defective toys

04:25.099 --> 04:26.974
Were made before
they caught the mistake.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.267
This you remember,

04:28.394 --> 04:31.436
But every year,
our anniversary evades you.

04:31.522 --> 04:33.480
Don't embarrass me
in front of the other blades.

04:33.565 --> 04:35.107
[snickering]

04:35.192 --> 04:37.484
Vomit book guy is on the boat?

04:37.569 --> 04:39.569
Ugh, cruise ruined.

04:39.655 --> 04:41.989
What do you have against
the comic book guy?

04:42.116 --> 04:45.242
I walked into his store
two weeks ago...

04:45.327 --> 04:47.619
I know this is weird,
but I actually drew

04:47.705 --> 04:49.663
A comic book of my own.

04:49.832 --> 04:51.206
[comic book guy]
hmm.

04:51.333 --> 04:53.417
Check it out.
He's half-croc, half-gator,

04:53.460 --> 04:54.835
And full prankster.

04:54.962 --> 04:58.213
Huh. Wow. You know what?
I'm really impressed.

04:58.382 --> 05:00.132
I'm going to fax
this right away

05:00.259 --> 05:03.593
To my friends at
"man, you suck publishing."

05:04.763 --> 05:05.846
[gasping]

05:05.973 --> 05:08.849
[laughs] you suck!

05:08.934 --> 05:10.434
[all laughing]

05:10.519 --> 05:12.352
I swear to god,
one day I'm going to

05:12.438 --> 05:15.063
Get my revenge
on comic book guy.

05:16.442 --> 05:17.983
♪

05:18.027 --> 05:20.193
[lively chatter]

05:20.321 --> 05:22.696
I hate this stupid baby
dress-up cruise.

05:22.781 --> 05:24.698
And why can't I be uncle fester?

05:24.867 --> 05:28.035
I'm bald, and I already own
several black muumuus.

05:29.121 --> 05:32.080
Ooh. Wait, this stuff doesn't
have punny names, does it?

05:32.166 --> 05:34.041
No, it's just like
any other cruise,

05:34.126 --> 05:36.960
Infinite food
for gluttonous slobs.

05:38.005 --> 05:40.964
Taika, why are you eating
all by yourself?

05:41.050 --> 05:42.716
To maintain energy
for all my writing,

05:42.843 --> 05:45.677
Directing, acting,
and rakish smirking.

05:45.763 --> 05:47.346
Plus, it's in my cruise rider.

05:47.431 --> 05:50.307
I also get a cabin facing
the sunrise and the sunset,

05:50.434 --> 05:51.433
Unlimited vegemite,

05:51.560 --> 05:54.561
And the top tier
of any seafood tower.

05:54.646 --> 05:55.687
Ah...

05:55.814 --> 05:57.522
Hmm... Hmm?

05:59.693 --> 06:00.776
Oh!

06:00.861 --> 06:02.277
Now on display,

06:02.363 --> 06:06.156
The exquisitely flawed
radioactive x-gentleman,

06:06.241 --> 06:10.660
Aka wolveractive man,
aka radio-verine.

06:10.829 --> 06:13.038
[crowd exclaims]

06:14.208 --> 06:15.832
Oh, look out. [grunts]

06:15.918 --> 06:17.417
Don't give that guy money.

06:17.503 --> 06:19.086
He's a dream-crushing jackass

06:19.171 --> 06:20.754
And he doesn't deserve
dollar one.

06:20.881 --> 06:25.050
I hope one day someone destroys
the thing you love most.

06:25.928 --> 06:27.094
[crowd exclaims]

06:27.137 --> 06:29.179
[carl]
somebody turned off the lights.

06:30.265 --> 06:32.140
-[crowd gasping]
-[gasps]

06:32.267 --> 06:34.393
[lenny]
the doll's head. It's gone.

06:34.520 --> 06:37.396
Speak to me, oh, headless
radioactive collectible.

06:37.523 --> 06:42.442
Oh, sweet suffering mate.
Let me share in your distress.

06:42.569 --> 06:44.569
[singing in japanese]

06:46.407 --> 06:48.073
Who could have done
such a thing?

06:48.200 --> 06:50.409
Who c-- [stammers]

06:50.536 --> 06:52.661
Oh, the agony!

06:52.830 --> 06:54.871
I wager bart simpson did this.

06:54.998 --> 06:56.581
He had the motive, means

06:56.667 --> 06:58.542
And he's a notorious stinker.

06:58.627 --> 07:02.170
That is a recipe for murder.

07:02.214 --> 07:06.007
And look at the three tiny
scratch marks on bart's cheek.

07:07.177 --> 07:10.762
No one murders a doll
on my ship. To the brig.

07:10.848 --> 07:12.347
[to<i> the addams family</i> theme]
♪<i> ba-da-da dum, ba-da-da dum</i> ♪

07:12.433 --> 07:14.599
♪<i> ba-da-da dum</i> ♪
d'oh! D'oh!

07:17.855 --> 07:19.813
I swear, I didn't
kill that doll.

07:19.982 --> 07:21.189
Stop lying, boy.

07:21.316 --> 07:24.025
I can't believe you ruined
my dream cruise.

07:24.153 --> 07:25.569
You hate this cruise.

07:25.654 --> 07:28.613
No, I hate the theme
and the people and the boat.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.532
But I love the food.

07:32.578 --> 07:35.078
Mr. And mrs. Simpson,
I know it's hard for you

07:35.164 --> 07:37.747
To see your son in
this tiny cruise ship jail.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.416
It is.

07:39.501 --> 07:40.917
Well, don't you worry.

07:41.044 --> 07:42.294
Tomorrow he'll be taken ashore

07:42.421 --> 07:44.921
And locked in
a full adult prison.

07:45.048 --> 07:48.133
-No!
-[gasps]
-but with all the amenities...

07:48.260 --> 07:49.217
Okay.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.678
The amenities are
a notorious prison gang.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.597
They really hate children.

07:53.682 --> 07:55.223
-No!
-No!

07:58.187 --> 08:01.188
Lis, I know it looks bad,
but I'm really scared.

08:01.223 --> 08:02.814
I swear I didn't do it.

08:02.900 --> 08:04.274
I don't know.

08:04.359 --> 08:06.193
You've beheaded
many of my dolls,

08:06.320 --> 08:09.237
From malibu stacy
to fire island frank.

08:09.364 --> 08:11.656
Oh, those aren't valuable.
They're yours.

08:11.700 --> 08:14.534
Bart, you've lied to me
so many times before,

08:14.703 --> 08:16.119
How could I ever believe you?

08:16.205 --> 08:18.580
Okay, but this time
I'm telling the truth,

08:18.749 --> 08:22.167
And to prove it, I'm gonna
own up to all my past lies.

08:22.211 --> 08:23.418
[inhales sharply]

08:23.462 --> 08:25.253
That time when the dog
buried your saxophone

08:25.297 --> 08:27.005
In the garden, he had some help.

08:27.049 --> 08:28.256
When malala called you
on your birthday

08:28.383 --> 08:30.550
To tell you to suck lemons,
that was me.

08:30.594 --> 08:32.761
That time you woke up in
a bathtub full of garlic knots--

08:32.888 --> 08:34.721
I get it, I get it.
You're terrible.

08:34.806 --> 08:37.390
Okay, I figure
I only get one time to say,

08:37.476 --> 08:40.268
"lis, you gotta believe me
no matter what."

08:40.395 --> 08:42.812
Right now,
I am playing that card.

08:42.856 --> 08:45.857
I did not destroy that doll.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.610
Oh, my god. I believe you.

08:49.696 --> 08:51.112
-[angry crowd clamoring]
-oh.

08:53.367 --> 08:55.242
The only way
to clear bart's name

08:55.327 --> 08:57.035
Is to figure out
who really did it.

08:57.162 --> 08:59.538
But I can't do it all by myself.
I need help.

08:59.706 --> 09:00.705
I'll help you.

09:00.832 --> 09:02.415
No, hang on,
let me try that again.

09:02.626 --> 09:04.876
I'll help you! Nailed it.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.837
Taika waititi? Seriously?

09:07.923 --> 09:09.881
You'll help me
exonerate my brother?

09:09.967 --> 09:11.716
Of course. Why? I'll tell you.

09:11.843 --> 09:13.218
Because I have
a medical condition

09:13.303 --> 09:15.554
Where I have to be
multitasking at all times.

09:15.681 --> 09:18.598
Well, my brother can't be
the only person on this ship

09:18.684 --> 09:20.141
Who hated comic book guy.

09:20.185 --> 09:21.685
So, I guess we'll just
have to question

09:21.853 --> 09:24.187
Every passenger on the manifest.

09:24.314 --> 09:26.273
Why don't we start with
fans of the taika-verse?

09:26.400 --> 09:30.068
Whoops, that's everyone.
[laughs]

09:30.153 --> 09:31.319
Let's go.

09:31.405 --> 09:34.114
I hate comic book guy
and I hated that doll

09:34.241 --> 09:36.741
Because it originally
belonged to me.

09:36.868 --> 09:38.326
[gasps]

09:40.330 --> 09:41.746
[gasps]

09:42.833 --> 09:45.417
Oh. Oh. Ooh.

09:45.586 --> 09:48.128
Oh, oh. Oh. Ooh! Ooh.

09:48.213 --> 09:51.089
Hi. Excuse me,
but I will take this, uh,

09:51.174 --> 09:54.134
Non-priceless,
completely valueless garbage

09:54.261 --> 09:58.305
-Off of your hands for, uh, $11.
-Huh?

09:58.432 --> 10:01.808
But, dad, I think it might
be worth a lot more.

10:01.977 --> 10:03.893
Who cares, milhouse?

10:04.062 --> 10:07.022
This is two $5 footlongs
and a weird cookie.

10:07.149 --> 10:11.359
Hey, luann, anniversary dinner
is back on, baby.

10:13.155 --> 10:14.863
I didn't destroy
that action figure,

10:14.990 --> 10:16.823
But I sure had a motive.

10:16.908 --> 10:18.867
A clear motive.

10:19.828 --> 10:22.078
I don't know why
you're interrogating me.

10:22.247 --> 10:25.290
I have no bone to grind with
that comic book chap.

10:26.251 --> 10:28.877
Really?
Even after comic book guy

10:28.962 --> 10:30.420
Led an online troll army

10:30.547 --> 10:34.007
To demand you be fired
and replaced in this?

10:34.176 --> 10:37.177
[announcer]
<i> from the producers of</i>
mad max<i> comes a vision</i>

10:37.220 --> 10:39.304
<i> So dark, so violent</i>

10:39.431 --> 10:41.514
<i> And so wacky.</i>

10:41.600 --> 10:43.433
<i> Sideshow mel.</i>

10:43.518 --> 10:48.104
We'll kill them all,
or my name isn't dick dastardly.

10:48.231 --> 10:51.566
<i> And timothée chalamet</i>
<i> as muttley.</i>

10:51.693 --> 10:53.652
[wheezing laugh]

10:55.739 --> 10:57.572
Curse that funny-book fiend.

10:57.616 --> 10:59.741
He mobilized both
the hanna-barbarians

10:59.868 --> 11:01.660
And the wack-olytes against me

11:01.787 --> 11:04.287
In a devastating
online petition.

11:04.373 --> 11:06.247
[lisa gasps]

11:06.333 --> 11:07.874
[rumbling]

11:08.001 --> 11:09.250
First of all,
that looks so good,

11:09.378 --> 11:11.461
I'm surprised
I didn't direct it.

11:11.630 --> 11:13.380
Did I? October was crazy.

11:13.465 --> 11:16.424
But mel, would your
bone-trembling anger

11:16.510 --> 11:17.509
Lead you to destroy

11:17.594 --> 11:20.470
Comic book guy's
most prized possession?

11:20.597 --> 11:22.722
It would! But it didn't.

11:22.849 --> 11:24.974
But it could! And if I did,

11:25.018 --> 11:27.602
I would lie about it to you now!

11:27.729 --> 11:30.522
But I'm not. But I would!

11:33.151 --> 11:35.110
Why are you
wasting your time with me?

11:35.237 --> 11:37.529
I love my greasy snowman husband

11:37.698 --> 11:40.407
And his tragic blooper
of an action figure.

11:40.450 --> 11:43.660
We have security footage
that says differently.

11:48.291 --> 11:52.961
It's true, I hated that
injection-molded monstrosity.

11:53.130 --> 11:55.255
When I first met comic book guy,

11:55.298 --> 11:57.590
I was his priceless collectible.

11:57.676 --> 11:59.134
But now, when we make love,

11:59.261 --> 12:01.970
My husband calls out
the doll's serial number.

12:02.097 --> 12:06.182
I just want back my sweet
comic book gaijin.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.226
[sobs]

12:11.314 --> 12:14.482
So many passengers could have
committed doll-icide.

12:14.526 --> 12:15.900
Hmm.

12:16.027 --> 12:17.360
Poor bart. Ah, but geez,

12:17.529 --> 12:20.989
Look at the mess
he left in our cabin.

12:21.908 --> 12:22.907
[gasps]

12:23.034 --> 12:26.745
Oh, dear god.

12:26.872 --> 12:28.288
I didn't think bart did it

12:28.457 --> 12:30.373
But then I found
this radioactive head

12:30.459 --> 12:33.126
From the decapitated doll
in bart's stuff.

12:33.170 --> 12:35.587
He looked me right in the eyes

12:35.630 --> 12:37.547
And said he didn't do it.

12:37.632 --> 12:39.591
I can never trust him again.

12:39.718 --> 12:41.134
-[cries]
-oh, sweetie,

12:41.178 --> 12:44.554
You've just learned
one of life's hardest lessons.

12:44.639 --> 12:47.015
Sometimes, no matter
how much you love someone,

12:47.142 --> 12:49.642
They're just
going to let you down.

12:49.728 --> 12:51.269
For your mother, it's me.

12:51.313 --> 12:53.521
Just try to get
some sleep, honey.

12:53.690 --> 12:57.734
Bart will still be
horribly guilty in the morning.

13:00.739 --> 13:01.738
[sighs]

13:01.865 --> 13:03.323
-[knock on door]
-hmm?

13:05.494 --> 13:07.076
Rainer wolfcastle?

13:07.162 --> 13:08.661
There is something
I must tell you

13:08.747 --> 13:12.490
About the night of the fanquet
and subsequent toy murder.

13:12.626 --> 13:13.958
When everything went dark,

13:14.127 --> 13:16.252
I was wearing
my night-vision goggles,

13:16.379 --> 13:18.963
From my upcoming film
<i> the night-vision goggler.</i>

13:19.007 --> 13:20.673
[gasps] did you see who did it?

13:20.708 --> 13:23.843
Patience, fräulein.
I did see the culprit,

13:23.929 --> 13:27.722
And I am about to tell you
who he or she is.

13:27.891 --> 13:30.725
Watch as the words
emerge from my mouth.

13:30.894 --> 13:34.312
The doll murderer
is<i> nein</i> other than--

13:34.356 --> 13:35.688
Ouch.

13:35.732 --> 13:39.526
I will be passing out now
and all of these things.

13:39.694 --> 13:41.236
[groans]

13:41.321 --> 13:42.362
[gasps]

13:50.121 --> 13:52.705
[groans] damn it.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.085
Ugh.

14:00.340 --> 14:03.174
Lisa. Are you also up
dusting for prints?

14:03.301 --> 14:04.968
That's what I call
eating leftover food

14:05.136 --> 14:07.053
Off people's room-service trays.

14:08.765 --> 14:10.431
I don't care!

14:11.434 --> 14:14.060
If one more
horrible thing happens,

14:14.187 --> 14:15.895
I'm going to lose it.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.230
[kumiko screams]

14:17.399 --> 14:21.734
My sweet comic book guy is gone.

14:21.862 --> 14:24.445
Of course he is.

14:24.489 --> 14:25.613
I mean...

14:25.657 --> 14:27.448
[shouts]

14:31.496 --> 14:33.580
Bart's in jail,
our one credible witness

14:33.748 --> 14:34.664
Just got sucker-shielded,

14:34.749 --> 14:36.040
Comic book guy is missing,

14:36.167 --> 14:38.126
And we're still no closer
to solving the case.

14:38.295 --> 14:39.961
So many twists and turns.

14:40.046 --> 14:41.754
What kind of
murder mystery is this?

14:41.840 --> 14:44.340
Stop talking, taika waititi.

14:44.509 --> 14:45.550
That's it.

14:45.635 --> 14:47.176
I know who murdered the toy.

14:47.262 --> 14:48.887
But I just need one thing:

14:49.055 --> 14:52.515
An audience to watch me
milk the big reveal.

14:52.642 --> 14:55.351
The murder of comic book guy's
action figure

14:55.437 --> 14:58.938
Was committed
by comic book guy himself.

14:59.065 --> 15:01.274
Based on a hunch,
I wrote to lloyd's of london,

15:01.401 --> 15:04.527
And I got this response
from lloyd himself. Good guy.

15:04.571 --> 15:07.614
Comic book guy had the doll
appraised and insured

15:07.741 --> 15:10.617
For 935,000 british pounds.

15:10.660 --> 15:12.035
[all exclaiming]

15:12.162 --> 15:13.411
So, he turned off the lights

15:13.496 --> 15:15.955
And murdered
the plastic action man himself

15:16.041 --> 15:17.415
For the insurance money.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.459
But then he knew
that we were onto him,

15:19.544 --> 15:21.544
Or, let's face it,
I was onto him.

15:21.630 --> 15:23.421
So, he took flight
in the dead of night,

15:23.548 --> 15:25.965
But not before planting
the doll's head in bart's cabin,

15:26.051 --> 15:27.842
And knocking out
the one witness to the crime,

15:27.969 --> 15:30.762
Washed-up action star
rainier wolfcastle.

15:30.847 --> 15:32.305
That's fair.

15:32.432 --> 15:33.765
[moans]

15:33.934 --> 15:35.600
Now comic book guy's probably

15:35.727 --> 15:37.852
On a tropical beach somewhere
sipping mai tais.

15:37.896 --> 15:40.396
Little does he know
that his heinous crime

15:40.523 --> 15:43.691
Has been exposed by me,
master sleuth

15:43.777 --> 15:46.027
And star of the upcoming reboot

15:46.112 --> 15:48.363
<i> Kiwi's big adventure,</i>

15:48.490 --> 15:49.948
Taika waititi.

15:50.033 --> 15:51.532
[cheering]

15:51.701 --> 15:54.494
Wow, he really did it.

15:57.040 --> 15:58.665
Oh, my god.

15:58.792 --> 16:00.833
How could I have been so stupid?

16:00.961 --> 16:04.337
Amazing work, taika waititi.

16:04.422 --> 16:06.381
I know you just
cracked the case,

16:06.466 --> 16:08.675
But I have a little
theory of my own.

16:08.760 --> 16:10.468
Does anyone want to hear it?

16:10.553 --> 16:11.761
[all]
no!

16:11.846 --> 16:14.389
Oh, come on, people.
What's the harm?

16:14.474 --> 16:15.723
Thank you, taika.

16:15.809 --> 16:17.308
Now, as you recall,

16:17.352 --> 16:20.728
There were only two of these
irregular radioactive man dolls

16:20.897 --> 16:22.981
Made in the whole world.

16:23.066 --> 16:25.024
-Oh, I remember.
-[murmurs of agreement]

16:25.068 --> 16:27.485
What if the owner
of the other doll

16:27.654 --> 16:29.112
<i> Received some bad news</i>

16:29.239 --> 16:31.406
<i> And broke their action</i>
<i> figure in a fit of rage?</i>

16:31.449 --> 16:35.076
<i>And then what if that owner came</i>
<i> on this cruise specifically</i>

16:35.120 --> 16:38.830
<i>To swap out their broken figure</i>
<i>for comic book guy's intact one</i>

16:38.957 --> 16:41.541
<i> So that they could secretly</i>
<i>possess the only radioactive man</i>

16:41.668 --> 16:44.210
<i> With wolverine claws</i>
<i> left in existence?</i>

16:44.337 --> 16:47.755
And I just discovered something
quite interesting,

16:47.882 --> 16:49.882
Thanks to the ship's
onboard wi-fi,

16:50.051 --> 16:52.635
Which is spotty at best.

16:54.055 --> 16:55.722
According to this website,

16:55.765 --> 16:57.640
That second doll was sold

16:57.767 --> 16:59.350
In wellington, new zealand,

16:59.436 --> 17:02.645
Where they spell "colour"
with a "u."

17:02.731 --> 17:06.941
Now, who on this boat do we know
comes from new zealand?

17:07.027 --> 17:09.360
Well, that's
a very clever theory.

17:09.446 --> 17:10.903
But if it's a crime
to be from new zealand,

17:11.031 --> 17:14.282
You'd have to arrest both guys
from flight of the conchords.

17:14.325 --> 17:17.076
What are their names again?
Fred and jimothy?

17:17.912 --> 17:19.162
You might be right,

17:19.330 --> 17:21.873
But consider that the shield
that incapacitated

17:21.958 --> 17:23.833
The only witness to the crime

17:23.918 --> 17:26.502
Seems to be covered with goo.

17:26.588 --> 17:29.714
What manner of goo?

17:29.799 --> 17:32.175
Dad, I know this is a weird ask,

17:32.302 --> 17:34.552
But would you mind
licking this-- oh.

17:34.637 --> 17:35.887
Ugh. Ew.

17:36.014 --> 17:38.473
Salty. Yeasty.

17:38.558 --> 17:41.476
Ugh. With hints
of malty grossness.

17:43.271 --> 17:44.270
Vegemite,

17:44.397 --> 17:47.148
The favorite food of
taika waititi.

17:47.275 --> 17:51.611
Or should I say fave-o-u-rite.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.529
[crowd muttering]

17:53.615 --> 17:55.823
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What about the scratch marks

17:55.909 --> 17:58.159
On bart simpson's face?
Those had to come from

17:58.203 --> 17:59.619
The tiny claws
on the doll he broke.

17:59.704 --> 18:03.998
Did they? Or maybe they came
from this seafood fork.

18:04.042 --> 18:05.541
My dad was selfishly shoveling

18:05.668 --> 18:07.960
<i> Pre-shucked shellfish</i>
<i> down his shrimp-shaft--</i>

18:08.046 --> 18:10.213
<i> One take [chuckles]--</i>
<i> and he accidentally</i>

18:10.373 --> 18:12.715
<i> Scratched bart on his cheek.</i>

18:12.801 --> 18:14.884
That silver-haired
multi-hyphenate

18:15.053 --> 18:16.719
Is guilty as sin.

18:16.763 --> 18:18.429
[chuckles] not without

18:18.556 --> 18:21.015
One more piece of
damning evidence, I'm not.

18:21.101 --> 18:23.476
You can't just
tear my cabin apart!

18:23.603 --> 18:24.894
You need a warrant!

18:24.979 --> 18:28.272
No, we don't.
We're in international waters.

18:28.316 --> 18:30.149
We're in the middle of
lake springfield.

18:30.276 --> 18:32.568
I can see the lard lad statue
from here.

18:32.695 --> 18:36.781
Here it is, comic book guy's
original doll unbroken.

18:36.866 --> 18:40.201
Damn it. Yes, it's true,
lenny. I did it.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.870
I threw my new zealand
radioactive man across the room

18:42.997 --> 18:44.872
When I found out
the streamer was shelving

18:44.999 --> 18:47.708
The second season of my series
without airing it.

18:47.794 --> 18:49.585
For tax purposes?

18:49.712 --> 18:51.087
Yes, for tax purposes.

18:51.214 --> 18:53.506
So I hatched this plan
because I needed the money

18:53.591 --> 18:57.385
To throw into my already
enormous pile of money.

18:57.428 --> 18:58.302
[handcuffs clink]

18:58.388 --> 19:00.429
You haven't seen the last of me.

19:00.557 --> 19:02.974
I've got powerful friends
in new zealand.

19:03.101 --> 19:07.687
Hobbits, orcs, lorde,
ents, melanie lynskey,

19:07.772 --> 19:09.272
The "how bizarre" guy.

19:09.315 --> 19:11.023
We are a powerful nation.

19:11.109 --> 19:12.859
[shrieks] ow! Ow!

19:12.902 --> 19:15.653
There is one thing
I can't figure out.

19:15.780 --> 19:17.613
What happened to comic book guy?

19:17.699 --> 19:19.615
I mean, we looked everywhere.

19:19.701 --> 19:23.369
[gasps] except the one place
he would never go.

19:25.790 --> 19:28.708
Oh, my sarcastic darling.

19:28.793 --> 19:30.418
What happened to you?

19:30.545 --> 19:32.044
Permit me to explain.

19:32.130 --> 19:34.088
[homer]
oh, more explaining?

19:34.215 --> 19:38.676
[comic book guy]
<i> when lisa and taika waititi</i>
<i> began questioning suspects,</i>

19:38.761 --> 19:40.511
<i> I set up a surveillance device</i>

19:40.597 --> 19:44.515
<i>Because I wanted to mock their</i>
<i>inept methods of interrogation.</i>

19:44.601 --> 19:46.767
<i> I hate comic book guy,</i>

19:46.895 --> 19:48.853
<i> But then again,</i>
<i> so does everyone.</i>

19:48.938 --> 19:50.438
<i> He smells like baked beans</i>

19:50.523 --> 19:52.106
<i> That have been left out</i>
<i> in the sun.</i>

19:52.233 --> 19:54.150
<i> I loathe his voice.</i>

19:54.319 --> 19:57.570
<i> Who speaks with such</i>
<i> exaggerated affectation?</i>

19:57.655 --> 19:58.863
[comic book guy]
<i>no one should ever have to hear</i>

19:58.990 --> 20:00.489
<i> What people</i>
<i> actually think of them.</i>

20:00.575 --> 20:04.452
Apparently, I am not a beloved
quirky character, like kramer.

20:04.495 --> 20:08.122
Instead, I am widely reviled,
like the guy who played kramer.

20:08.208 --> 20:11.125
So, I hid here,
surrounded only by shame

20:11.211 --> 20:14.212
And whatever these
metal things are.

20:14.297 --> 20:16.422
Mmm! [grunts happily]

20:16.549 --> 20:18.633
I don't want to get
all sincere and emo,

20:18.760 --> 20:20.009
But thanks, lisa.

20:20.094 --> 20:21.418
You never lost faith in me.

20:21.429 --> 20:24.972
Well, if I'm being
totally honest...

20:25.808 --> 20:27.516
...I never did.

